body:
I haven't seen the previous error and don't really have an intuition for it. Can you tell us exactly what command you ran?

For the second part -- your data size has to be a multiple of 16, since the UNet has 4 downsampling and 4 upsampling levels.  You could, for example, pad your images to the next multiple of 16.

I used this command

_python train_miccai2018.py /Users/xiao/Desktop/lab/software/voxelmorph-master/train --gpu 0 --model_dir /Users/xiao/Desktop/lab/software/voxelmorph-master/mymodel_

in  _/Users/xiao/Desktop/lab/software/voxelmorph-master/train_ there is **test_vol.npz**
which gave you the first or the second error?
It gave me the first error. Sorry for the confusion.

This setup trains well for me (just tried it). Perhaps you have a very old version of tensorflow? I would recommend looking online, as this seems to be a [tensorflow issue](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/26769) beyond voxelmorph?
Thank you very much for your help!
@X-ma how did you solve this issue
@X-ma How do you get `test_example.txt` and `labels.mat` in `test_miccai_2018.py` or `test.py`? Please give an example. Thanks.

@DownStone `labels.mat` is included in the `data` folder, and `test_examples.txt` should simply include lines like:
`/fulll/path/to/test_example_1.nii, /full/path/to/test_example_1_seg.nii`
